contentrichtext.text: '''Björkö''' ([[Swedish language|Swedish]] for "[[Birch]] Island") can signify: # In [[Sweden]]: ## [[Björkö, Ekerö|Björkö]], a [[Mälaren|Lake Mälaren]] island in [[Ekerö Municipality]], [[Stockholm County]], the location for the excavation and [[World Heritage Site]] [[Birka]]. ## [[Björkö, Öckerö|Björkö]], an island in [[Öckerö Municipality]], [[Västra Götaland County]]. ## [[Björkö, Haninge|Björkö]], an island in [[Haninge Municipality]], Stockholm County. ## Björkö, the southern part of [[Väddö]] island in northern [[Roslagen]], [[Norrtälje Municipality]], Stockholm County. (Also a former parish there.) ## [[Björkö, Västervik|Björkö]], an island in [[Västervik Municipality]], [[Kalmar County]]. # In [[Finland]]: ## [[Björkö, Houtskär|Björkö]], one of the main islands of the former municipality [[Houtskär]] in the [[Archipelago Sea]]. ## [[Björkö (Korsholm)|Björkö]], a [[Kvarken]] island in [[Korsholm|Korsholm Municipality]], [[Ostrobothnia (region)|Ostrobothnia]]. ## [[Björkö, Kumlinge|Björkö]], an island and a village in [[Kumlinge|Kumlinge Municipality]] in the [[Åland Islands]]. ## [[Björkö, Korpo|Björkö]], an island in the former municipality [[Korpo]] in the [[Archipelago Sea]]. # In [[Russia]]: ## The Swedish name for [[Primorsk, Leningrad Oblast|Primorsk]] and the [[Beryozovye Islands]] in the [[Leningrad Oblast]], ## The [[Treaty of Björkö]], signed by [[Nicholas II of Russia]] and [[William II, German Emperor|William II]] of the [[German Empire]] in 1905. {{disambiguation}}
